From: Romain Francoise <rfrancoise@debian.org>
Date: Thu, 24 Feb 2011 23:26:42 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 06/10] Emacs is built without RPATH.

On Debian, binaries must not contain an RPATH section (and in this
case, it's redundant with system-wide library paths).

Signed-off-by: Julien Danjou <julien@danjou.info>
---
 autogen/configure | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/autogen/configure b/autogen/configure
index e44b44a..10fa5b7 100755
--- a/autogen/configure
+++ b/autogen/configure
@@ -9428,7 +9428,7 @@ LD_SWITCH_X_SITE_RPATH=
 if test "${x_libraries}" != NONE; then
   if test -n "${x_libraries}"; then
     LD_SWITCH_X_SITE=-L`echo ${x_libraries} | sed -e "s/:/ -L/g"`
-    LD_SWITCH_X_SITE_RPATH=-Wl,-rpath,`echo ${x_libraries} | sed -e "s/:/ -Wl,-rpath,/g"`
+    LD_SWITCH_X_SITE_AUX_RPATH=
   fi
   x_default_search_path=""
   x_search_path=${x_libraries}
